source: Access documentation page for the REST API
Connects Drupal to the OpenAPI Javascript Library
No OpenApi generator plugins are currently available.
Please visit the OpenAPI UI module for information on these interfaces and to discover others.
The specifications provide the documentation on some of Drupal's apis following OpenAPI (aka Swagger) standards.
There are no plugins available for exploring the OpenAPI documentation.
These json files can be used in tools such as the Swagger Editor to provide a more detailed version of the API documentation or Swagger Codegen to create an api client.
You can install one of the below projects to view the API Specifications from with your site.
You must enable a REST or API module which supports OpenApi Downloads, such as the Core Rest and JSON:API modules.
